<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p><strong>02，Argumentative Writing的重要性</strong></p>
<p>Debate is a process that involves formal discussion on a particular topic. In a debate, opposing arguments are put forward to argue for opposing viewpoints. Debate occurs in public meetings, academic institutions, and legislative assemblies. </p>
<p>辩论是涉及对特定主题进行正式讨论的过程。在辩论中，提出了相反的论据以主张相反的观点。辩论发生在公开会议，学术机构和立法议会中。</p>
<p>In speaking we “debate” someone to oppose their point of view. In writing we use an <strong>argumentative/discussion essay</strong>. </p>
<p>在发言中，我们“辩论”某人以反对他们的观点。在写作中，我们使用论证/讨论论文。</p>
<p>In today’s setting, people obtain solutions after making an informed decision. From an educational point of view, the purpose of making students write such essays is so that schools can evaluate a) their knowledge of a topic, and b) their critical thinking skills. </p>
<p>在当今的环境中，人们在做出明智的决定后可以获得解决方案。从教育的角度来看，使学生撰写此类论文的目的是使学校可以评估a）他们对某个主题的知识，以及b）他们的批判性思维能力。关于批判性思维怎么做，大家可以参考：http://www.baydue.com/news/faq/255.html</p>
<p><strong>03，Argumentative Writing的组成部分</strong></p>
<p>An argumentative/discussion essay has the following structure: </p>
<p>论证/议论文具有以下结构：</p>
<p><strong>Title:</strong> Tells exactly what the discussion will be about. </p>
<p><strong>标题</strong>：准确说明讨论的内容</p>
<p><strong>Introduction:</strong> Introduces the people/groups who have different views and opinions </p>
<p><strong>介绍</strong>：介绍有不同意见的人 /团体 </p>
<p><strong>Body:</strong> Has a series or arguments/reasons for andagainst the topic in structured and organized paragraphs. Uses words such as:“and, as well as, additionally, also, furthermore” to add points validating the writer’s argument. It also uses contrast words such as: “but, although, on the other hand, however, on the contrary, alternatively” when doing a counterargument. </p>
<p><strong>正文</strong>：在结构化和有组织的段落中对该主题有一系列或一系列的论点/理由。使用诸如：“以及，以及，此外，还”来添加验证作者论点的观点。在进行反驳时，它也使用诸如“但是，即使，另外一方面，然而，相反的，相对的”的对比词。</p>
<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> Sums up the arguments and restates the writer’s point of view and why. </p>
<p><strong>结论</strong>：总结论点，重申作者的观点及其原因。</p>